    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available for the discerning enthusiast is this 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD3S, a masterclass in lightweight engineering and 50/50 weight distribution. At its heart is the 13B-REW twin-rotor engine, featuring a sequential twin-turbocharger setup that provides linear power delivery throughout the rev range. The drivetrain is anchored by a precise five-speed manual and a Torsen limited-slip differential, ensuring optimal torque vectoring out of corners. The suspension remains true to its roots with a four-wheel double-wishbone configuration, offering unmatched tactile feedback. This example features a refreshed cooling circuit with a high-capacity aluminum radiator and a vacuum system overhaul to maintain boost integrity. While the exterior displays minor signs of road use, the mechanical fundamentals\u2014including compression and turbo transition\u2014are robust. This is a driver-focused FD prepared for the canyons or the track.",
